cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.AI

This paper uses text mining and sentiment analysis techniques to predict stock market tendencies and prices based on news articles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with techniques for retrieving relevant information from large collections of data. The paper also uses machine learning algorithms such as support vector machines (SVM), which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques, which is a subfield of cs.CL (Computational Linguistics). The paper also deals with financial data, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Economics) and uses AI techniques for prediction, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
